---
import { C, FONT } from "../infographicTokens";
---

<svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" viewBox="0 0 720 320" fill="none" aria-hidden="true">
  <title>Sizing airflow from load</title>
  <desc>CFM equals BTU per hour divided by 1.08 times delta T, with the 1.08 constant broken out and a worked example.</desc>

  <text x="360" y="34" text-anchor="middle" fill={C.dark} font-family={FONT} font-size="16" font-weight="700">Sizing airflow from load</text>

  <!-- Main formula -->
  <rect x="120" y="58" width="480" height="62" rx="10" fill={C.primaryLight} stroke={C.primary} stroke-width="1.5" />
  <text x="360" y="98" text-anchor="middle" fill={C.dark} font-family={FONT} font-size="20" font-weight="800">CFM = BTU/hr &#247; (1.08 &#215; &#916;T)</text>

  <!-- Constant breakout -->
  <rect x="160" y="138" width="400" height="52" rx="8" fill={C.panelBg} stroke={C.border} />
  <text x="360" y="160" text-anchor="middle" fill={C.muted} font-family={FONT} font-size="11" font-weight="600">The 1.08 constant</text>
  <text x="360" y="180" text-anchor="middle" fill={C.dark} font-family={FONT} font-size="13" font-weight="700">0.24 (specific heat) &#215; 60 (min/hr) &#215; 0.075 (lb/ft&#179;) = 1.08</text>

  <!-- Worked plug-in -->
  <rect x="80" y="210" width="560" height="64" rx="10" fill={C.blueLight} stroke={C.blue} stroke-width="1" />
  <text x="360" y="234" text-anchor="middle" fill={C.blue} font-family={FONT} font-size="11" font-weight="700">Worked example: a 6,000 BTU/hr room, 20&#176;F supply-to-room &#916;T</text>
  <text x="360" y="258" text-anchor="middle" fill={C.dark} font-family={FONT} font-size="14" font-weight="800">6,000 &#247; (1.08 &#215; 20) = 6,000 &#247; 21.6 &#8776; 278 CFM</text>

  <text x="360" y="302" text-anchor="middle" fill={C.muted} font-family={FONT} font-size="11">CFM = BTU/hr &#247; (1.08 &#215; &#916;T). The 1.08 constant bundles air&#8217;s specific heat, density, and minutes per hour.</text>
</svg>
